      • createMeasure

        public Measure createMeasure(String displayId,
                             Double numericalValue,
                             URI unit)
                      throws SBOLValidationException
        Creates a child measure for this measured object with the given arguments, and then adds to this measured object's list of measures.

        This method first creates a compliant URI for the measure to be created. It starts with this measured object's persistent identity URI, followed by the given display ID, and ends with this measured object's version.

        Parameters:
        displayId - The displayId identifier for this
        numericalValue - the numerical value for this measure
        unit - the unit of this measure
        Returns:
        the created measure
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if any of the following SBOL validation rules was violated: 10201, 10202, 10204, 10206, 13501, 13502, 13503, 13504, 13505,

      • removeMeasure

        public boolean removeMeasure(Measure measure)
        Removes the given measure from this measured object's list of measures.
        Parameters:

      • getMeasure

        public Measure getMeasure(String displayId)
        Returns the measure matching the given display ID from this measured object's list of measures.

        This method first creates a compliant URI for the measure to be retrieved. It starts with this measured object's persistent identity, followed by the given display ID, and ends with this measured object's version.

        Parameters:
        displayId - the display ID of the measure to be retrieved
        Returns:
        the matching measure if present, or null otherwise

      • clearMeasures

        public void clearMeasures()
        Removes all entries of this measured object list of measures. The list will be empty after this call returns.

        This method calls removeMeasure(Measure) to iteratively remove each measure owned by this object.
